First combine the factors inside the radical.

\[
\sqrt{\frac{36 r^{10}}{16 r^{5}}}
      =\sqrt{\left(\frac{36}{16}\right) r^{10-5}}
      =\sqrt{\frac{36}{16}\, r^{5}}
      =\sqrt{\frac{9}{4}\, r^{5}}
\]

Split the square root over the fraction and the power of \(r\):

\[
\sqrt{\frac{9}{4}}\;\sqrt{r^{5}}
        =\frac{3}{2}\;\sqrt{r^{5}}
\]

Write \(r^{5}\) as \(r^{4}\,r\) so that \(r^{4}\) is a perfect square:

\[
\frac{3}{2}\;\sqrt{r^{4}\,r}
        =\frac{3}{2}\;\sqrt{(r^{2})^{2}}\;\sqrt{r}
        =\frac{3}{2}\;r^{2}\sqrt{r}
\]

Thus the simplified form is  

\[
\boxed{\dfrac{3}{2}\,r^{2}\sqrt{r}}
\]

(If it is required to account for sign, use \(|r^{2}|=r^{2}\) when \(r\ge 0\); in many algebra texts the variable is assumed non-negative inside square roots.)

